dc_description_s: This data layer represents addresses for Green County, Wisconsin in 2016. [To be used by Green County Sheriff's Dispatcher's through their third party E911 dispatching and reporting system created by Spillman Technologies. Data created in conjunction with State E911 update grant. Features were derived from a variety of sources including deeds, descriptions, subdivision maps, certified survey maps, easements, and right of way maps. These source materials were of varying scale and date. This coverage provides a representation of the geometry and topology of tax parcels within the County, and is suitable as a reference layer within the County's GIS.]
uw_supplemental_s: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. For additional information, please see original license/data sharing agreement where applicable. Best known date is 5/10/2015. For complete metadata documentation and online dataset download, please visit http://www.co.green.wi.gov/localgov_departments_details.asp?deptid=115&locid=148. [The Land Information Office is part of the Green County Treasurer's Office. The office provides maps, with overlays of parcels, addresses, aerial photos, school districts, soils, and supervisory districts. You may purchase a hard copy map of any portion of Green County by completing the Request for County Maps Form. If you wish to purchase a digital map, you must also complete the License Agreement. Send completed form(s) along with the correct payment to Green County Treasurer, 1016 16th Avenue, Monroe, WI 53566. Duties The Land Information Office coordinates land information projects within the county, between County & Local Governments or State and Local Governments and among local governmental units, the federal government, and the private sector. Public Information A Green County Map Viewer is available to the public for information regarding property ownership, tax roll information (tax amount, assessment values, etc) and an aerial photo by address. The map viewer has recently been updated and new tools have been incorporated in an effort to make the access to information easier. If you have questions, please contact the Treasurer's Office at 608-328-9435.]
